  <description><![CDATA[<p>Verbier is without a doubt one of the worlds top resorts, with a huge amount of skiing and that's without counting the neighbouring resorts you can access through it in the 4 Vallées region, which collectively offer 410 kilometres of pistes. Skiers and snowboarders can find some of the most challenging and varied terrain in the Alps in Verbier, a beautiful, modern resort constructed in the traditional chalet style. Verbier is the largest resort in the area, and lies in a sunny, south facing bowl with spectualar views of the surrounding peaks. From the ski area's highest point, Mont Fort (3330 m), you can take in a fantastic view of the Matterhorn, the Combins, and the Mont Blanc ranges.</p>
<h2>Skiing and Snowboarding in Verbier</h2>
<p>Home to the largest ski area in Switzerland, skiers and snowboarders have access to 410km of varied slopes, whether this is your first time on the slopes or you are a snow sport fanatic, there are endless possibilities. <span> The 4 Vallées ski area is made up of six resorts comprising of; <span class="c5aZPb" data-enable-toggle-animation="true" data-extra-container-classes="ZLo7Eb" data-hover-hide-delay="1000" data-hover-open-delay="500" data-send-open-event="true" data-theme="0" data-width="250" data-ved="2ahUKEwiBot6a0YH_AhWrTEEAHYsqCfcQmpgGegQIExAD"><span class="JPfdse" data-bubble-link="" data-segment-text="Verbier">Verbier</span></span>, Bruson, La Tzoumaz, Nendaz, Veysonnaz and Thyon. All of which have their own individuality. </span></p>
<h2>Where to stay in Verbier</h2>
<p>We offer two hotels in Vebier both of which have excellent locations in the centre of the resort. </p>
<h2>Bars and restaurants in Verbier</h2>
<p>If you're out and about on the slopes, you can choose from a wide variety of bars and restaurants, many of which serve lunch with incredible views of the mountains. Try the 'Plat du Jour' (plate of the day) for reasonably priced regional specialties at one of the charming huts during lunch. <br />As soon as the sun goes down, there are a wide variety of bars to choose from. Whether you're searching for an idyllic spot to unwind or a bustling bar to dance the night away, you'll be able to find it here.</p>
<h2>What's included in an Inghams holiday to Verbier</h2>
<p><span>Flights, transfers and accommodation based on half board.  Optional add ons include equipment hire, lift pass and tuition, please see the 'Ski extras' tab below for more information on these.</span></p>]]></description>
