  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners skiing in Verbier</strong></p>
<p>Les Esserts is one of the most popular places for beginning skiers and snowboarders to go given its short, gentle slopes conveniently positioned next to the Hameau bus stop and restaurant terrace. </p>
<p>The Le Rouge nursery area features two slopes that run from the top of the the village of Carrefour to the Brunet bus stop, which is located in the centre of the village. Beginner skiers and snowboarders can make use of the variable speed drag lift to access a slightly more inclined slope, making it an ideal place to progress after spending some time on Les Esserts.</p>
<p>After you have gained some confidence, the La Chaux located higher up the mountain, is a nice spot to progress. There are some pleasant blue runs which wind with a south facing direction.  This area is an excellent choice for putting what you've learned at ski school into practise.</p>
<p><strong>Intermediates skiing in Verbier</strong></p>
<p>With around 400km of pistes across the 4 <em>Vallées you'll be spoilt for choice.  </em>Intermediate skiers and snowboarders can choose between the sunny La Chaux region, the gentle slopes of the Lac des Vaux, and the wide, gliding runs of the Attelas and the Combes.  Bruson is a <span>great place for bad weather skiing as well as some fun off-piste. </span></p>
<p><strong>Advanced skiing in Verbier</strong></p>
<p>The challenging steep runs, the exceptional off-piste terrain, and the abundance of black runs experts will have a great time exploring the area. The area's renowned slopes include the exhilarating black run that begins at Mont Fort, as well as the 'itinerary' routes which begin at Col des Gentaines and Mont Gelé. Even the most experienced will find a challenge. For those who are looking for challenging but thrilling descents will want to either head straight to the Col de Chassoure to test their skills on the Chassoure-Tortin "wall", a steep and heavily moguled face.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding in Verbier</strong></p>
<p>With hardly a draglift to be found in the local area, Verbier is a great resort for snowboarders. Try the snowpark or boarder cross at La Chaux, not forgetting endless powder runs between dotted throughout the area.</p>
<h4>Freestyle </h4>
<p>Head to La Chaux for the Verbier snowpark, which has a variety of kickers, boxes, and rails made for freestyle skiers and boarders of all skill levels. The Audi Skicross, a 700-meter run for all skill levels nearby the snow park, gives you the chance to test your skills on banked turns and a range of jumps. </p>
<p>The mini-kilometer sprint is also in La Chaux. This involves skiing down the course as fast as possible while racing against your friends for the quickest run of the day.</p>]]></generalInformation>
