  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<h3>Restaurants, food and drink</h3>
<p>If you feel like Savoyard specialities, swanky Michelin star meals or Italian classics you wont have to look to far. There are plenty of restaurants in Verbier to suit all tastes and budgets. </p>
<p>At lunch time many restaurants both on and off the mountain offer a 'plate of the day' (<span>Plat du Jour) usually consisting of seasonal produce which is worth looking out for as its good value for money. With a range of cosy alpine restaurants dotted around on the mountain, it will be a hard choice where to stop for lunch. </span><span></span></p>
<h3>Après, bars and nightlife</h3>
<p>After a day on the mountain, there is no shortage of places to enjoy a few drinks and some live music. Whether you prefer to enjoy wine in the late afternoon sun or dance on the tables in your ski boots with a beer  in hand, Verbier offers a variety of fantastic locations when the lifts close for the day.</p>
<p>If you're looking for late-night entertainment, Verbier has a number of bars and clubs that stay open until the early hours of the morning. Undoubtedly one of the best venues in the Alps, The Farm Club is an essential stop on any trip to Verbier.</p>
<h3>Spas and relaxation</h3>
<p>Take a break from skiing and head to the Away Spa for a day of relaxation. The facility features two heated swimming pools, hammams, saunas, jacuzzies, and the FIT exercise area, which is equipped with modern equipment.</p>
<h3>Shopping </h3>
<p>Verbier has a number of high fashion shops, as well as handcrafted souvenirs and sporting goods businesses throughout the resort. </p>
<p>Rental stores and sports shops are often open until late in the day to allow you to make the most of your time on the mountain before returning your equipment at the end of your last day.</p>
<h3>Things to do in Verbier</h3>
<h4>Sports Centre </h4>
<p>Verbier Sport Centre <span>will keep you occupied when its just a bit too snowy to go on the slopes. It has a climbing wall, squash courts, in and outdoor tennis courts and a sports hall. There is also an indoor swimming pool to keep you occupied. </span></p>
<h4><span>Ice skating and curling </span></h4>
<p>Skate around the outdoor ice rink at the <span>Parc de Loisirs, or play a game of Eisstock (similar to curling) for a bit of afternoon entertainment. </span></p>
<h4><span>Tobogganing </span></h4>
<p><span>Swap yours skis or snowboard for a toboggan and whizz down the dedicated La Tzoumaz toboggan run in the Savoleyres area. Be sure to have your cameras ready as the view from the top of the run is incredible. </span></p>
<h4>Snowshoeing &amp; Winter hiking</h4>
<p>Rather than speeding downhill, take to the mountains on foot and explore the beautiful landscape surrounding Verbier. </p>
<h4>Alpine Museum</h4>
<p>The museum offers an enlightening tour through history, where visitors can learn about life in the Alps throughout the centuries. Providing information on a variety of topics, including  agriculture, cattle, life in the Alps, working the vines, small industry crafts, the local textile industry, transportation, energy, housing, and customs.</p>
<h4>Parapenting</h4>
<p>Take off from the summit of Les Ruinettes, which is 2,200 metres above sea level and experience Verbier from the sky.  An experience that will take your breath away. </p>]]></thingsToDo>
